EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 072300 UTC
THIS PERIOD SHOULD START WITH A DEEP LOW WITH CENTRAL PRESSURE 955 OFF
SWERN ICELAND WITH THIS FEATURE THEN MOST LIKELY MOV SLWY NE AND FLN INTO
THE NEW WORKING WEEK MOST LIKELY COMING TO LIE IN THE VICINITY OF THE ARCTIC
OCEAN BY MIDWEEK. THIS SHOULD ACT TO DISPLACE AN INTSF HIGH OVER EERN EUROPE
EWARDS AS A NEW HIGH DEVELOPS OVER THE MID-ATLANTIC. THIS NEW HIGH SHOULD
THEN MOV INTO THE SW APPROACHES TO END THE PERIOD. A SWATHE OF GALES AND
EVENTUALLY SEV GALES SHOULD SPREAD BODILY EWARDS INTO WERN PORTPATRICK FM
LATE SUNDAY. FM HERE AS THIS SWATHE CONTINUES BODILY NE THE FOCUS SHOULD
SHIFT TO NERN AND NWERN PORTPATRICK FOR THE REMAINDER OF THE FOUR-DAY PERIOD
WITH PERIODS OF SEV GALES PERHAPS BRIEFLY EASING GALE. BY THIS TIME SERN
PORTPATRICK SHOULD SEE NO HAZARDOUS WINDS
